# nanoGPT — Decoder-Only Transformer from Scratch

A character-level language model built entirely from scratch in PyTorch. Trained on Shakespeare's plays (~1MB), it generates new text that mimics Shakespeare's style, vocabulary, and formatting — without copying any original text.

This project implements the core architecture behind models like GPT: token and positional embeddings, multi-head causal self-attention, feedforward layers, residual connections, layer normalization, and dropout — all in a single, readable training script.

## Sample Output

```
GLOUCESTER:
I would be us:
Slew me to thrice join'd a
vesses rise. She must lord.

DUCHESS OF YORK:
If we thank you now of the guest.

KING EDWARD IV:
O, which let me me thou?
What I was a guestitulE?

STANLEYCUS:
With life.

POMPEY:
Ay, from man, and give men.
```


## Architecture

The model follows the standard decoder-only transformer design:

```
Input tokens
    ↓
Token Embedding + Position Embedding
    ↓
┌─────────────────────────────┐
│  Transformer Block (×6)     │
│  ┌────────────────────────┐ │
│  │ LayerNorm              │ │
│  │ Multi-Head Attention   │ │
│  │ (6 heads, causal mask) │ │
│  │ + Residual Connection  │ │
│  ├────────────────────────┤ │
│  │ LayerNorm              │ │
│  │ FeedForward (4× expand)│ │
│  │ + Residual Connection  │ │
│  └────────────────────────┘ │
└─────────────────────────────┘
    ↓
LayerNorm → Linear → Softmax → Next Token Prediction
```

## Hyperparameters

| Parameter | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| Embedding dimension (`n_embd`) | 192 |
| Attention heads (`n_head`) | 6 |
| Transformer blocks (`n_layer`) | 6 |
| Context length (`block_size`) | 64 |
| Batch size | 32 |
| Learning rate | 3e-4 |
| Dropout | 0.2 |
| Optimizer | AdamW |

